    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/nagaraja-credibility-assessment-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The overall credibility assessment for COU1 is Accepted. Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed their required gradation levels. The single below-requirement factor (Test conditions, achieved Gradation 2 vs. required Gradation 3) is acknowledged and documented; however, the quantitative validation metrics (E/uval < 1.96 for all QoIs, percent differences < 10%) demonstrate that the model predictions are well within the pre-specified acceptance bounds across all three quantities of interest. The credibility assessment team, in consultation with the regulatory affairs group, determined that the single test-condition gap does not materially undermine the overall credibility conclusion given the strength of the quantitative output comparison evidence and the direct correspondence between the validation activity and the COU.",
